<title>USA: Computervision sees $45 mln Q2 charge.</title>
<headline>Computervision sees $45 mln Q2 charge.</headline>
<dateline>BEDFORD, Mass. 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Computervision Corp said Monday that following the completion of the sale of its Open Service Solutions unit to CVSI Inc it will incur a $45 million pre-tax charge against 1997 second quarter earnings.</p>
<p>The company said it is taking the charge because the disposition of the Open Service unit will enable it to rationalize its cost structure and finalize its evolution into a pure software solutions company.</p>
<p>It added that as a result of the sale, Computervision expects to improve its business model and operating margins.</p>
<p>Computervision received $32.6 million in cash in the transaction and a $10 million subordinated note from CVSI.</p>
